  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Evidence carries explicitly low confidence scores and wide uncertainty bounds on several factors; these are documented honestly with full rationale. The decision is Accepted with documented residual risk acknowledgement: the team determined that the uncertainty is bounded, the conservative threshold margin provides adequate safety buffer, and no weakener fires on this package.",
