      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5-gradation2",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residuals (all < 1e-5) and mass imbalance (< 0.01%). Round-off error assessed as negligible at double precision. Solver error contribution to NIH uncertainty estimated at < 0.5% via sensitivity study. Gradation 2 achieved. Note: required level set at 2 for this factor at MRL 5 given that discretization error dominates and is separately assessed at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5-gradation2",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst against documented simulation plan. Boundary condition assignments, turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), and hemolysis model parameter inputs verified against source publications. No use errors identified. Peer review checklist completed and archived. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5-gradation3",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty is the largest identified source of uncertainty in this assessment. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is known to have wide inter-laboratory variability in exponents. This is explicitly documented: confidence in the model form is rated LOW. However, the Monte Carlo analysis propagating the full published range of exponent values (alpha: 0.785±0.12, beta: 2.416±0.31) yields 90th-percentile NIH predictions that remain 22% below the clinical threshold. The team accepts Gradation 3 as achieved because the uncertainty is bounded and the conservative margin is sufficient for MRL 5 with a Class III device. Residual model-form uncertainty is documented as an accepted limitation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5-gradation3",
      "rationale": "Input parameter uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo for blood viscosity (±8%), hemolysis model exponents, inlet flow rate (±3%), and rotational speed (±0.5%). Full distribution of 1500 Monte Carlo samples archived. Sensitivity analysis identifies hemolysis model exponents as dominant input uncertainty contributor (62% of output variance). All input distributions documented with literature sources. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl5-gradation2",
      "rationale": "Three pump specimens from the same manufacturing batch used for bench testing. Inter-specimen variability in NIH measurements: CV = 4.1%. Sample size (n=3 specimens × 5 conditions × 3 replicates = 45 measurements) is adequate for Gradation 2 at MRL 5. Explicitly noted that a larger sample across manufacturing batches would increase confidence; this limitation is documented. Gradation 2 achieved and accepted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
